HEADWORD: Ottawas
<hw>Ot"ta*was</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>; <sing>sing.
<singw>Ottawa</singw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></sing>. <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>A
tribe of Indians who, when first known, lived on the Ottawa River. Most
of them subsequently migrated to the southwestern shore of Lake
Superior.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

